High-level language, easy to read, great for scripting and AI, slower than compiled languages

Common object sizes in 64-bit CPython:

| Type | Typical size |
| --- | --- |
| bool | 28 bytes |
| int | 28 bytes for small integers, grows as the number gets bigger |
| float | 24 bytes |
| complex | 32 bytes |
| empty str | 49 bytes, then grows with contents |
| empty bytes | 33 bytes, then grows with contents |
| empty list | 56 bytes, plus about 8 bytes per element slot |
| empty tuple | 40 bytes, plus about 8 bytes per item |
| empty dict | 64 bytes or more, grows by hash table capacity |

Python variables hold references to objects. Sizes vary by Python implementation, version, and machine.
